<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,543,750]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,171,544,570]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,257,550,567]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">REMARKS</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,264,544,570]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">.</emphasis>
This is a slightly smaller 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[566,689,544,569]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[566,689,544,569]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with body length of about 
<quantity box="[1095,1218,544,570]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="39.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="38.0">38–40 mm</quantity>
and wing spans of about 
<quantity box="[220,314,580,606]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.14" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="114.0">114 mm</quantity>
. The infuscation on the distal apical cell veins and ambient veins of the wings rather than only bronzing of the distal wings quickly distinguishes this species from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[913,1036,616,641]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[913,1036,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in 
<collectingCountry box="[1144,1199,616,642]" name="Peru" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1239,651,678]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,543,750]" box="[199,1239,651,678]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,219,652,678]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[219,350,658,675]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">DISTRIBUTION</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[350,357,652,678]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">.</emphasis>
The species has been reported previously only from 
<collectingCountry box="[950,1043,651,677]" name="Ecuador" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[1058,1226,651,678]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref106666" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
